var _story_ = {
    "8003": [
        {
            "_id": 11,
            "Story": "A {F#girl}{M#boy}, Trailblazer, decides to travel with the Astral Express to eliminate the threat of the Stellaron."
        },
        {
            "_id": 12,
            "Story": "You don't remember much.<br>You're not from around here, nor did you come from elsewhere. You're not really going anywhere—<br>Just then, that indistinct voice whispers into your ear. That sorrowful and tender persuasion, that deceptive goading...<br>The seeds take root. You open your eyes, and the speaker is no longer there.<br><br>But there are more and more voices, and they are getting clearer and clearer.<br>Some give easygoing care, some calmly provide advice, some speak firm support, and some gift gentle direction...<br>You see the silken thread being woven to form tomorrow.<br><br>A huge beast descends from infinity,<br>golden pupils stare down from the darkness,<br>and you are no longer abandoned by the past.<br>You will also set upon a long journey,<br>and the thorns you have stepped on have become your path.<br><br>The train whistles, wishing you a successful journey to the coming future<br>...by your own will."
        },
        {
            "_id": 13,
            "Story": "You have arrived at the \"City of Preservation.\"<br>Behind the snow curtain, the wind lashes like steel blades, but the kindling burns on.<br>Distant lands won't hear them, and the earth trembles in kind, with only the wailing crowds braving the wind.<br><br>After facing foreign enemies, the Eternal Freeze, and reality's fissures, a rot begins to fester within the fort.<br>You try lending a helping hand, but are forsaken.<br>Some once looked down on you and misunderstood you, but still you stood by their side and helped them find their way.<br>More care about you and worry about you. They face their suffering, and find the cure for the distressed.<br>Eventually, they come to your side.<br><br>In the ice and snow, you are like a fire, protecting the soul of this world<br>...Even though you must scorch yourself day and night."
        },
        {
            "_id": 14,
            "Story": "The harmonious music guides you to stumble into the sweet dream, as syrup and soda fill your throat.<br>The festival is grand, the crowd boisterous, and strangers cast on disguises to meet up in the dream.<br>You view to your hearts' desires the wondrous and otherworldly views, and part ways when dewdrops shimmer with the break of dawn —<br>When the pitch-black midnight has just begun.<br><br>The clock hands go tick-tock, and death follows closely like a shadow.<br>You are placed onto the table as a bargaining chip, but manage to win for yourself the right to uncover the secret.<br>You bring with you the dreams of the dead and continue on the road that they did not walk, facing the enemies they could not defeat—<br><br>The false god rises in the conglomeration of the multitude's wishes, and the unanimous song of the gazillions drowns out your existence.<br>Those walking on different roads take up each other's hands,<br>your melodies interweave with each other, faint but imperishable like the lights in a long night.<br>One after one, people startle awake from their dream. That tiny song finally merges into a deafening roar in the end, tearing free of the dream's curtains.<br><br>The eternal sweet dream scatters in a fleeting instant, and you finally understand why people slumber<br>— They do so towards a dawn freed from dreams."
        },
        {
            "_id": 15,
            "Story": "Look, in The Eternal Land, a nameless epic unfolds.<br>Listen. The wind's ballad sings the elegy of Era Nova, and witnesses the golden blood flowing through slumbering flowers, as the Coreflames sustain the scarred earth.<br>Like seeds about to perish, poems fade into obscurity.<br><br>For false endings shackle the story's beginning.<br>Count the cold fluorescent lights, sting the eyes that pray for dawn.<br>Time has yet to flow, the sun is set to die. Is this the story's climax, or the finale?<br>No, there's still... one final stroke.<br><br>And so you leave traces of \"Trailblaze\" on every page, where falls turn into ascents on another end.<br>You race through the mire of memories, using billions of Coreflames to scorch the frigid data sequences, and catching the shattered seed germs.<br>When a new blank page appears, you make your mark. It, too, will form ripples toward the past.<br><br>Glimmering lights twinkle in the night sky of blank memories, where a shooting star yet to come has been entrusted with the anticipation of eternity.<br>Thirteen heartbeats sing proudly for the Flame-Chase Journey, for that was the land they deeply cherished.<br>The first page of the story unfolds once more, inscribed with prophecies of life.<br><br>Listen! The wind sings a melody, the Seeds of Memory grow among the stars, for<br>the cosmos now knows the name, \"Amphoreus.\""
        }
    ]
}

